de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.jrdf2vec.walk_generation.walk_generators

Class MemoryWalkGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.jrdf2vec.walk_generation.walk_generators.MemoryWalkGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMidEdgeWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IMidTypeWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IMidWalkCapability, IMidWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IMidWalkWeightedCapability, INodeWalksDuplicateFreeCapability, IRandomWalkCapability, IRandomWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IWalkGenerationCapability, IWalkGenerator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JenaOntModelMemoryWalkGenerator, NtMemoryWalkGenerator, NxMemoryWalkGenerator

    public abstract class MemoryWalkGenerator
extends Object
implements IWalkGenerator, IMidWalkCapability, IMidWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IRandomWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IMidWalkWeightedCapability, IMidEdgeWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, IRandomWalkCapability, IMidTypeWalkDuplicateFreeCapability, INodeWalksDuplicateFreeCapability
    Memory based walk generator using the TripleDataSetMemory data structure. These kind of walk generators load the complete model into memory.

        public List<String> generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity(String entity,
                                                      int numberOfWalks,
                                                      int depth)
        Weighted mid walk: If there are more options to go forward, it is more likely to go forward. The walks are duplicate free.
        Specified by:
        generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity in interface IMidWalkWeightedCapability
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which walks shall be generated.
        numberOfWalks - Number of walks to be performed per entity.
        depth - The depth of the walk. Depth is defined as hop to the next node. A walk of depth 1 will have three walk components.
        Returns:
        List of walks.
